RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $2,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances Only).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SASQUATCH RIDE tracked the decent pace into the turn, maintained a two wide path between rivals along the bend, was roused three wide into the stretch, confronted PHANTOM DROP approaching mid-stretch, battled with that rival to deep stretch, took command at the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in a drive to prevail. PHANTOM DROP broke through the gate prior to the start, was away in good order and set the decent pace to the turn, was pressed to the quarter marker by TRABIESO AVELITO, shook free into upper stretch then was confronted by SASQUATCH RIDE nearing the furlong marker, resisted against that rival's bid into deep stretch but could not match strides in the final stages and was outfinished, while besting the rest. TRABIESO AVELITO stumbled leaving the break and was off a step slowly, stalked the decent early pace while outside of rivals, pressed the pacesetter from the three path to the quarter marker, swung to the four path for the drive, re-rallied and vied for the lead at mid-stretch, weakened in the final stages and held clearly in the end for third. HUMBLEBUMBLEFUMBLE was away a bit slowly and chased from the inside early on, could not keep pace into upper stretch and did not offer a response in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Sasquatch Ride
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace,btwn 2wide turn,bid 3wide stretch,wore down foes

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 100. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. One Such Race Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Sta rter Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUE SERA SIR RALPH broke alertly and assumed command in the early stages, set a moderate pace while prompted through the backstretch run, was well handled while carving the fractions into the far turn, spurted clear in upper stretch, drew off under moderate urging in the drive and was wrapped up in the final yards as much the best. LOOKIN FOR REVENGE settled along the inside in the run into the first turn, tracked the moderate pace from a ground saving position into the far turn, angled three wide into the drive, was no match for the winner in the final furlong and ran on to be best of the rest. LIL MIRACLE MAN was forwardly placed into the first turn, attended to the decent pace through the backstretch run, kept attendance to QUE SERA SIR RALPH to the quarter marker, could not match strides into the drive, weakened in the final stages and was outfinished for second, while clear in the end for third. SUNNY SPOT settled just off of the early pace, was well positioned while in the two path through the backstretch run, slipped to the rail along the second turn, lacked the needed response in the drive and gave way. IL CAPITANO was hard to load prior to the start, lunged at the break and was off a step slowly, was hard to place while a bit rank into the first turn and chased outside of rivals into the backstretch run, ran in pursuit to the half-mile marker, could not keep pace on the far turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 96. Waiver Claiming Purse 25000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter R aces For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances Only).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAMARA MINE raced close to the decent early pace, stalked the pacesetter while three wide along the turn, made a steady advance on MUCHA WOMAN in upper stretch, drew to even terms with that rival inside of the furlong marker, took command heading to the sixteenth-pole and drove clear in the final stages. LADY'S SERMON took up and was bothered leaving the start and was off slowly, chased the decent early pace while outside of a rival, gained ground while three wide along the turn, was coaxed along in the four path into upper stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, finished well in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to secure second. MUCHA WOMAN broke out at the start and bothered neighboring rivals leaving the break, showed early speed and set a pressured pace into the turn, shook free along the bend and carved out decent fractions to the quarter marker, held TAMARA MINE at bay to mid-stretch, could not match strides with that rival into the final furlong, weakened in deep stretch and was just edged for second, while holding clearly for third. CRYSTAL PROOF was prominent in the early running and pressed the decent pace to the turn, lost position while saving ground on the turn, chased the leaders into upper stretch and gave way in the final stages. DRAW ME was bothered at the start by MUCHA WOMAN then in turn bothered LADY'S SERMON and was off a bit slowly, chased the decent early pace from the rear, saved ground to the quarter marker while trailing, angled two wide into the stretch and could not muster a late response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If A Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive A $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.)(Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The L ast Three Starts Preferred.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KRISTIN LEE broke sharply and showed good early speed, dictated terms to the turn and was well handled through the bend while carving solid fractions, extended the lead into upper stretch and drew clear in the final sixteenth in a good debut. CRYPTO CRUSH broke out at the start and was away slowly, trailed into the turn then advanced position along the bend while two wide, swung five wide for the drive, made a mild gain at mid-stretch, rallied in the final stages and could not reel in the winner but was up in the final strides to secure second. BIG CATTY was prominent in the early running and raced close to the quick pace while outside of rivals, ran in pursuit while three wide along the turn, chased KRISTIN LEE to mid-stretch, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and just missed for second while clear of the rest for third. SMILE BABY SMILE was forwardly placed early on and chased the solid pace from the inside, pressed from the rail along the turn, lost ground into the stretch and weakened in the final furlong. OUTER SUNSET chased the solid early pace, ran in pursuit while outside of rivals along the turn and came four wide into the stretch, was a bit green in the drive while racing on the left lead and did not offer a late rally. MISS PERU chased the solid early pace, raced two wide along the bend, could not keep pace into the stretch and tired. HANG ON lacked early speed, dropped back on the turn, lost contact into upper stretch and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE SANDY SURPRISE bobbled at the start then lagged behind the field while racing four or five wide down the backstretch, launched a bid with three furlongs to go while still racing wide, came into the stretch in the six path and sustained the rally through the stretch to just get up in the last jump. MIGHTY MATT tracked the early pace between a trio of horses down the back stretch, was being ridden from the half-mile marker but made steady forward progress through the turn, found a seam four wide turning for home, rallied strongly down the stretch, briefly had the advantage but lost the bob at the wire. SURPRISE FASHION bobbled at the start, recovered well then raced mid-pack through the early stages on the inside of a trio chasing the leaders, moved in tandem with MIGHTY MATT through the turn to get into contention, took the inside path into the stretch, got clear run at the leader and ran on well but was outfinished in the shadow of the wire. DAD BOD broke in a bit but quickly corrected, was hustled to the front and opened up a clear lead before running a quarter mile, was in hand through the turn, responded briefly when roused at the top of the stretch but could not hold on and weakened in the final furlong. DUMB LUCK broke sharply, dueled to the inside of DAD BOD early, switched to the three path before the turn, chased that foe to the stretch, came under pressure approaching the three-sixteenths marker and had nothing to offer down the stretch. RUNNING ON EMPTY outrun to the turn, had one beat with three furlongs to run then came up empty in the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke sharply, close up to stretch, bid turn, nothing to offer

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 93. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $32,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred.)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A Cla iming Price.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MICRO SHARE settled just off of the early pace, raced outside of rivals and came four wide into the backstretch run, advanced to stalk the moderate pace to the far turn, was asked for run three wide nearing the quarter marker, vied for the lead into upper stretch, took command inside of the furlong marker, was kept to task under firm urging to deep stretch, dug in in the final stages and held off the oncoming runner-up to prevail. STOIC LUNA was allowed to settle in the early running, improved position while outside of rivals along the backstretch run, raced four wide along the far turn, rallied while widest into the stretch and loomed approaching the furlong pole, closed willingly in the final sixteenth, could not get by the determined winner in deep stretch and was well clear of the rest for second. WORK TO LIVE was prominent into the first turn and attended to the pace while outside of rivals into the backstretch run, prompted the moderate pace to the far turn, confronted MADEIRA WINE approaching the quarter marker, battled with that rival into upper stretch and vied for the lead at the furlong marker, could not match strides with MICRO SHARE into the final furlong, weakened in the final sixteenth and just held for third at the wire. MADEIRA WINE broke alertly and established the early lead, set moderate fractions while prompted through the backstretch run, was challenged by WORK TO LIVE along the far turn, fought back against oncoming rivals to mid-stretch, faded in the final stages and just missed for third. BANDEENA bobbled leaving the start and was off a bit slowly, was unhurried while running in the three then four path along the first turn, settled along the backstretch run and came two wide into the second turn, was coaxed along three wide into the drive and did not threaten. LA REINE'S LEGACY stalked the early pace from the inside, raced close to the moderate pace through the backstretch run, lost position while two wide on the far turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and gave way. BOLD DAUGHTER settled along the inside early on, was well positioned along the backstretch run while saving ground, was outrun along the far turn and tired in the stretch drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: She's A Tiger S. PLEASANTON RACE 7 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 99. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. No nomination fee.$350 to enter, an additional $350 to start, or by supplementary nomination of $1,500 (includes all fees), by time of entry. $75,000 Guaranteed with $45,000 to the winner, $15,000 to se cond, $9,000 to third, $4;500 to fourth and $1,500 to fifth. Weight: Three-Year-Olds; 122lbs.; Older: 125 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes at a mile or over in 2023 allowed 2 lbs.; Non-winners of a twice other than at a mile or over allowed 4 lbs. Nomin ations closed Saturday, June 17, 2023 with 13 nominations. High weights preferred. Preference for horses with equal weights will be determined by 2023 non-claiming earnings.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASCENDANCY took back off of the contentious early pace and settled inside of a rival into the first turn, was unhurried through the backstretch run, was given her cue leaving the three-furlong pole and loomed two wide nearing the quarter marker, collared ANTHONYS CLEOPATRA in upper stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong marker and pulled away in the final stages. TWILIGHT EMPIRE was unhurried in the early running, settled outside of a rival and raced three then four wide into the backstretch run, maintained that four wide path into the far turn, gained ground nearing the quarter marker and came three wide for the drive, continued to advance approaching mid-stretch, could not keep pace with ASCENDANCY in the final furlong and was outkicked, while clear of the rest for second. ANTHONYS CLEOPATRA was asked to show early speed leaving the break, engaged with TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL and dueled through fast fractions into the backstretch run, continued to battle on the front end with that rival to the half-mile marker, shook free along the second turn, was collared by ASCENDANCY in upper stretch and chased that rival to the furlong grounds, yielded in the final furlong and was outfinished for second, while holding clearly in the end for third. CLOCKSTRIKESTWELVE settled off of the quick early pace, maintained a two wide path through the backstretch run and into the far turn, swung widest and came five wide into the stretch drive, was not able to impact the leaders in the stretch and passed tiring rivals in the final furlong. BUYBACK was forwardly placed while outside of rivals into the first turn, tracked the rapid pace through the backstretch run, raced two then three wide to the quarter pole, could not muster the needed response in the stretch and gave way. SMOOTHLIKEBUTTAH was allowed to settle in the early running, saved all of the ground through the backstretch run, trailed into the far turn, was coaxed along two wide into the stretch and did not factor in the drive. TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, engaged with ANTHONYS CLEOPATRA soon after the break and contested the pace with that rival along the first turn, dueled through fast fractions along the backstretch run, lost ground to ANTHONYS CLEOPATRA along the far turn, dropped back in the stretch and faded in the final stages. NAUGHTY NADINE (GB) tracked the rapid pace from the inside, raced closest to the dueling pacesetters through the backstretch run, lacked a response along the far turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HYDRO FROST hustled out of the gate but settled behind the pace, was prompted to keep up as the pace quickened before the turn, responded when asked in earnest to go after the leaders at about the five-sixteenths marker, swung five wide into the stretch, had difficulty changing leads for the length of the stretch but was able to sustain the run to win by a comfortable margin in the end. MY BUCKET LIST broke well, was able to press the issue on the front end but backed out of a potential speed duel to a tracking position, re-bid approaching the quarter pole, took the lead at the top of the stretch and ran on well under right handed urging but could not hold off the fast closing winner while well clear of the third horse. WESTERN SIERRA broke well, sat off the flank and to the outside of JERSEY BABE to the quarter pole, got the best of that rival before the stretch then had to contend with a challenge from MY BUCKET LIST to the outside, was unable to match strides with that one in deep stretch but held third. OUR NORTH STAR stumbled slightly then was bumped by SON OF SHANGHAI after the break, made up a bit of ground in the backstretch run, launched a bid from the five-sixteenths marker but stalled before mid-stretch and tired. CHELSIESDANZIGLITE got off to an awkward start, chased from an inside position down the backside and through the turn, continued to run at the same pace through the stretch and never made an impact. MIGHTY RULER hustled from the gate but was unable to challenge the early leaders, was kept to task while racing four wide through the turn, showed little. JERSEY BABE broke well, set a contested pace to the turn with WESTERN SIERRA applying pressure to the outside, hit a wall passing the quarter pole and was not persevered with from there. SON OF SHANGHAI veered out and bumped OUR NORTH STAR coming out of the gate, did not appear comfortable in the early going after that and was climbing down the backstretch, was allowed to setting into stride going into the turn but trailed the field throughout.
